---

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-bofu" id="pcfo-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">What a fractional CFO costs.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="pcfo-tldr-body">A fractional CFO at TechBrot is a <strong>monthly retainer of $3,000&ndash;$8,000+</strong>, accepted <strong>by application</strong> with limited capacity each quarter. Unlike bookkeeping &mdash; which is priced on transaction volume and the size of the close &mdash; the CFO retainer is priced on <strong>judgment and depth of involvement</strong>: how often you need strategic finance in the room, how many entities sit under you, whether there&rsquo;s a fundraise, board, or lender in play, and the cadence of the reporting and forecasting you need. The retainer is fixed, not hourly, and scoped per engagement after a free discovery call &mdash; the exact number in writing before you commit. This is advisory work: it is <strong>not tax filing and not audit or assurance</strong>, and it coordinates with your CPA rather than replacing one. Acceptance isn&rsquo;t guaranteed; senior engagements are limited.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="pcfo-different">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why it isn&rsquo;t priced like bookkeeping</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Judgment, not transaction volume.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Bookkeeping pricing is volume math. Count the transactions, the bank and credit accounts, the entities, the payroll runs &mdash; the fee tracks the size of the monthly close. The work is largely the same shape every month, so it prices cleanly as a recurring fixed fee.</p>
      <p>A fractional CFO is the opposite. The deliverable isn&rsquo;t a reconciled ledger &mdash; it&rsquo;s <strong>decisions you can defend</strong>: a forecast a lender will trust, a board package that survives questions, a pricing or hiring call backed by unit economics, a cash runway you can act on before it&rsquo;s a crisis. None of that scales with transaction count. A 30-transaction-a-month startup raising a seed round can need more CFO time than a 2,000-transaction business that just wants someone steering the quarter.</p>
      <p>So the retainer is priced on the <strong>depth of involvement the business actually needs</strong>, not on how busy the books are. That&rsquo;s also why it&rsquo;s accepted by application: senior strategic capacity is finite, and the engagement only works when the scope is honest on both sides.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pcfo-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Fractional CFO pricing, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="pcfo-ai-summary-body">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pcfo-drivers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What sets the retainer</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Four things move the monthly number.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Where you land in the $3,000&ndash;$8,000+ range is set by depth, not by how many transactions clear &mdash; these are the factors the discovery call surfaces.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for d in drivers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="team-card__role">{{ d.label }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pcfo-scenarios">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Representative scenarios</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where engagements tend to land.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Illustrative only &mdash; not quotes, not real clients. Your retainer is scoped per engagement after the discovery call and confirmed in writing.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">Representative fractional CFO retainer scenarios. Illustrative only; the exact retainer is scoped per engagement in writing.</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Situation</th>
            <th scope="col">Depth of involvement</th>
            <th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">Where it tends to land</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for row in scenarios %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.situation | safe }}</td>
            <td class="vs-table__concede">{{ row.depth | safe }}</td>
            <td class="vs-table__us"><strong>{{ row.range | safe }}</strong><span class="vs-table__concede">/mo</span></td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">Ranges are representative and never a quote. Every retainer is fixed, scoped per engagement after a free discovery call, and confirmed in writing &mdash; engagements are accepted by application, with limited capacity per quarter.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pcfo-application">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">By application</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Why this engagement is accepted by application.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Senior strategic finance can&rsquo;t be mass-produced. A fractional CFO carries a small number of engagements at a time because the role demands real context &mdash; on your numbers, your decisions, and the people relying on them. To protect that depth, TechBrot accepts a limited number of CFO engagements each quarter and takes them <strong>by application</strong>.</p>
      <p>The discovery call is where the fit is tested in both directions: what you need, what capacity exists, and whether a fractional CFO is even the right answer (sometimes the honest answer is cleanup-and-bookkeeping first, then advisory later). <strong>Acceptance isn&rsquo;t guaranteed.</strong> When an engagement is accepted, the retainer scope is delivered in writing &mdash; the exact monthly number, the cadence, and the deliverables &mdash; before anything begins.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pcfo-not">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What the retainer is &mdash; and isn&rsquo;t</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Advisory, not tax or audit.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>A fractional CFO retainer is <strong>advisory and strategic finance</strong>: forecasting, cash-flow strategy, KPI and board reporting, scenario and fundraise modeling, and the financial judgment behind operating decisions. It is delivered as a fixed retainer against a written scope &mdash; never hourly.</p>
      <p>It is <strong>not tax filing</strong> and <strong>not audit or assurance</strong>. TechBrot does not file your returns or issue audited financials; the fractional CFO <strong>coordinates with your CPA or EA</strong>, making sure the strategy and the books are ready for them, but tax and attestation stay with the appropriate licensed professional. If you don&rsquo;t have a CPA, the engagement helps you work with one &mdash; it doesn&rsquo;t replace one.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="pcfo-path">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">From question to retainer</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Four steps to a number in writing.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="flow" role="img" aria-label="The path to a fixed retainer: a free 30-minute discovery call, then a written scope within 3 business days, the monthly retainer in writing with no hourly billing, then the engagement begins with a named advisor.">
      <div class="flow__step flow__step--accent"><span class="flow__label">Free discovery call</span><span class="flow__sub">30 min &middot; no obligation</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Written scope</span><span class="flow__sub">within 3 business days</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Retainer, in writing</span><span class="flow__sub">no hourly billing</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Engagement begins</span><span class="flow__sub">named advisor</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pcfo-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you apply</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about fractional CFO cost.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pcfo-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="pcfo-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pcfo-next">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Next steps</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where to go next.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for card in nextCards %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ card.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ card.href }}">{{ card.cta }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
